history.text:
During her reign, notable reforms included (<htcite0>):
- eliminating part of the bureaucracy, simplifying communication between the people and the ruler;
- improving public education, with the hiring of dedicated teachers;
- promoting agricultural reforms, raising production to record levels;
- reforming the tax system;
- reopening the Silk Road, which had been interrupted since a plague in <htdate0>.

In addition to these reforms, one in particular deserves highlight, which is why we chose to isolate it: thanks to Wu Zetian's (武則天) reforms, there was some advancement in equality between men and women (<htcite1>).

#### The End

Power led her to paranoia, compounded by personal life issues that scandalized Chinese society, culminating in her abdication in the year <htdate1>.
